SIMPLE: frivolous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frivolous
<hw>Friv"o*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>frivolus</ets>; prob. akin to <ets>friare</ets> to rub, crumble, E.
<ets>friable</ets>: cf. F. <ets>frivole</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of little weight or importance; not worth notice;
slight; <as>as, a <ex>frivolous</ex> argument</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Given to trifling; marked with unbecoming levity;
silly; interested especially in trifling matters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His personal tastes were low and <qex>frivolous</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Trifling; trivial; slight; petty;
worthless.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Friv"o*lous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Friv"o*lous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Friz</ent>⟦br⟧
